As reported, excessive ROS irreversibly injuries DNA and lipids, and ultimately leads to cell apoptosis (
). H 2 O 2 , a common oxidant, could induce oxidative damage and increase the levels of ROS in cells (
). In next experiment, the capacity of compounds 1–3 to rescue H 2 O 2 -induced oxidative stress was investigated. The flow cytometric analysis showed that H 2 O 2 exposure effectively increased DCF positive ratio. But compounds 1–3 could ameliorate the situation prominently and the ROS levels were similar to control group (Fig. 7). These results suggested that compounds 1–3 reduced H 2 O 2 -induced ROS accumulation in SH-SY5Y cells, which might be arising from the restoration of the antioxidant defense system.

Mitochondrial dysfunction is proved to be one of the most emerging pathological process in neurodegenerative disorder (
). It is reported that, mitochondria is an important source of reactive oxygen species, and the increased ROS intensifies mitochondria dysfunction and cell injury (
). The decreased mitochondrial membrane potential (ΔΨm) was regarded as a significant indicator to denote mitochondrial dysfunction. As the result in Fig. 8 , the fluorescence intensity ratio between green and red significantly increased after treatment with H 2 O 2 treatment, which suggested that H 2 O 2 could induce mitochondrial dysfunction. This phenomenon was reversed in compound group, the percent of ΔΨm loss cells of which was reduced to 18.4%, 11.8% and 11.2%, respectively. The results suggested that compound 1–3 could protect SH-SY5Y cells from mitochondrial dysfunction induced by H 2 O 2 .
